%% ============================================================
%% UML SEQUENCE DIAGRAM — EduVidQA
%% ============================================================
%%
%% This diagram shows the exact order of events when a student
%% uses EduVidQA, from opening the page to receiving an answer.
%%
%% PHASE 1 — VIDEO SELECTION & AUTO-INGEST:
%%   1. Student opens the video page in their browser.
%%   2. Frontend embeds the YouTube player via IFrame API.
%%   3. Student pastes a YouTube URL.
%%   4. Frontend sends POST /process-video to the backend.
%%   5. Backend checks ChromaDB: is this video already indexed?
%%   6. If NOT indexed: runs full ingestion pipeline —
%%      download .mp4, extract transcript, extract frames,
%%      SSIM dedup, embed keyframes (Gemini), embed text (BGE-M3),
%%      store all embeddings in ChromaDB, delete the .mp4.
%%   7. If ALREADY indexed: skip straight to "ready".
%%   8. Backend responds: video is ready.
%%
%% PHASE 2 — WATCHING & ASKING:
%%   9. Student watches the video, pauses at 12:34.
%%   10. YouTube IFrame API reports getCurrentTime() = 754 seconds.
%%   11. Frontend displays "Timestamp: 12:34" (auto-updating).
%%   12. Student clicks the chat input — timestamp freezes.
%%   13. Student types their question and clicks Ask.
%%   14. Frontend sends POST /ask {video_id, question, timestamp: 754}.
%%
%% PHASE 3 — RETRIEVAL & ANSWER:
%%   15. Backend embeds the question using BGE-M3.
%%   16. ChromaDB performs hybrid search (text + visual cosine similarity).
%%   17. Returns top-K transcript chunks and nearest keyframes.
%%   18. Backend sends frames + transcript + question to Groq API
%%       (Llama 4 Scout 17B, a vision-language model).
%%   19. Groq returns the answer text.
%%   20. Backend scores the answer: Clarity 4.2, ECT 3.8, UPT 4.0.
%%   21. Backend returns answer + quality scores + source timestamps.
%%   22. Frontend displays the answer with badges in the chat.
%%   23. Timestamp resets to auto-mode for the next question.
%% ============================================================

sequenceDiagram
    actor Student
    participant UI as Frontend
    participant YT as YouTube API
    participant API as FastAPI
    participant Ingest as Ingest Pipeline
    participant VDB as ChromaDB
    participant LLM as Groq Llama 4
    participant Eval as Quality Eval

    Note over Student,Eval: Phase 1: Video Selection & Auto-Ingest

    Student->>UI: Opens video page
    UI->>YT: Embed YouTube player
    YT-->>UI: Player ready

    Student->>UI: Pastes YouTube URL
    UI->>API: POST /process-video {url}
    API->>API: parse_video_id(url)
    API->>VDB: is_indexed(video_id)?

    alt Video NOT indexed
        API->>Ingest: ingest_video(url)
        Ingest->>Ingest: Download .mp4 (yt-dlp)
        Ingest->>Ingest: Extract transcript (CSV)
        Ingest->>Ingest: Extract 1 frame/sec
        Ingest->>Ingest: SSIM dedup → N keyframes
        Ingest->>Ingest: Embed keyframes (Gemini Embed 2)
        Ingest->>Ingest: Embed transcript (BGE-M3)
        Ingest->>VDB: Store embeddings
        Ingest->>Ingest: Delete .mp4
        Ingest-->>API: {video_id, title, segments}
    else Already indexed
        VDB-->>API: cached
    end

    API-->>UI: {video_id, status: ready}

    Note over Student,Eval: Phase 2: Watching & Asking

    Student->>YT: Watches video, pauses at 12:34
    YT-->>UI: getCurrentTime() = 754 sec
    UI->>UI: Display Timestamp 12:34 (auto-updating)

    Student->>UI: Clicks chat input
    UI->>UI: Freeze timestamp at 12:34
    Student->>UI: Types question
    Student->>UI: Clicks Ask

    UI->>API: POST /ask {video_id, question, timestamp: 754}

    Note over API,LLM: Phase 3: Retrieval & Answer

    API->>VDB: retrieve(question, video_id, top_k=5)
    VDB->>VDB: Embed question (BGE-M3)
    VDB->>VDB: Cosine search (text + visual)
    VDB-->>API: top transcript chunks + nearest keyframes

    API->>LLM: generate_answer(frames + transcript + question)
    LLM-->>API: answer_text

    API->>Eval: score(question, answer)
    Eval-->>API: {clarity: 4.2, ect: 3.8, upt: 4.0}

    API-->>UI: {answer, sources, quality_scores}
    UI-->>Student: Display answer + badges + source timestamps
    UI->>UI: Reset timestamp to auto-mode
